	(2111,'_transient__sol_cache_872','a:3:{s:6:\"slider\";a:7:{i:877;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:112:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/27-Image-Carousel-Medical-Fraud-Slide-11.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:51:\"27 – Image Carousel – Medical Fraud – Slide 1\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:51:\"27 – Image Carousel – Medical Fraud – Slide 1\";s:7:\"caption\";s:411:\"Chances are you’ve heard that identity theft is a growing concern in America. But what about medical identity theft?  Your personal information is stored in many different databases and handled by lots of different people, which could make you a target for medical identity theft. [1]\n\nHere are some places where your medical identity is stored and what to look for when dealing with your medical information.\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:878;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:112:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/27-Image-Carousel-Medical-Fraud-Slide-21.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:51:\"27 – Image Carousel – Medical Fraud – Slide 2\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:51:\"27 – Image Carousel – Medical Fraud – Slide 2\";s:7:\"caption\";s:316:\"<strong>The Doctor’s Office: </strong> Doctor’s appointments are a necessity of life, but your medical records and personal information aren’t always 100% secure. Make sure to read your Explanation of Benefits (EOB) statement to be sure you’re not being charged for medical services you didn’t receive. [1]\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:873;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:111:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/27-Image-Carousel-Medical-Fraud-Slide-3.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:59:\"Pharmacy: Concerned Pharmacist Calling About a Prescription\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:59:\"Pharmacy: Concerned Pharmacist Calling About a Prescription\";s:7:\"caption\";s:298:\"<strong>The Pharmacy:</strong> Last time you checked, you didn’t order a prescription for Ritalin but somehow it’s showing up on your EOB statement. Identity thieves could use your personal information to fill prescriptions, so it’s really important to review all prescription statements. [1]\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:874;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:111:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/27-Image-Carousel-Medical-Fraud-Slide-4.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:38:\"Blood Bank: Nurse Talks to Blood Donor\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:38:\"Blood Bank: Nurse Talks to Blood Donor\";s:7:\"caption\";s:242:\"<strong>The Lab:</strong> Getting blood drawn isn’t always fun, but neither is getting your identity stolen. Pay close attention to your credit report to ensure you don’t receive a medical collection notice that you don’t recognize. [1]\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:875;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:112:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/27-Image-Carousel-Medical-Fraud-Slide-51.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:51:\"27 – Image Carousel – Medical Fraud – Slide 5\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:51:\"27 – Image Carousel – Medical Fraud – Slide 5\";s:7:\"caption\";s:260:\"<strong>Your Workplace: </strong>Enrolling in benefits means that you’re probably sharing a lot of personal data. If you’re denied insurance based on an existing condition that you never had, this could be a sign that you are a victim of medical fraud. [1]\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:876;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:112:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/27-Image-Carousel-Medical-Fraud-Slide-61.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:51:\"27 – Image Carousel – Medical Fraud – Slide 6\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:51:\"27 – Image Carousel – Medical Fraud – Slide 6\";s:7:\"caption\";s:323:\"<strong>Your Wallet:</strong> Between credit cards, loyalty rewards, and your driver’s license, your Social Security card may seem like just another item to stash in the wallet and go. It’s important, however to make sure your sensitive information is stored in a safe, secure location that only you have access to. [1]\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:1012;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:110:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/MetLife-Defender-Logo-Image-Galleries2.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:39:\"MetLife-Defender-Logo—Image-Galleries\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:39:\"MetLife-Defender-Logo—Image-Galleries\";s:7:\"caption\";s:298:\"Protect your medical identity no matter the location: MetLife Defender can help protect you by tracking your data and safeguarding your personal information. \n\n<a href=\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/medical-fraud-protection/\">Click here</a> to find out more about medical identity fraud.\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}}s:2:\"id\";i:872;s:6:\"config\";a:12:{s:4:\"type\";s:7:\"default\";s:12:\"slider_theme\";s:4:\"base\";s:12:\"slider_width\";i:800;s:13:\"slider_height\";i:450;s:10:\"transition\";s:4:\"fade\";s:8:\"duration\";i:5000;s:5:\"speed\";i:400;s:6:\"gutter\";i:20;s:6:\"slider\";i:1;s:7:\"classes\";a:1:{i:0;s:0:\"\";}s:5:\"title\";s:41:\"5 Places Your Medical Records Are at Risk\";s:4:\"slug\";s:41:\"5-places-your-medical-records-are-at-risk\";}}','no'),
