	(5523,853,'_sol_slider_data','a:3:{s:2:\"id\";i:853;s:6:\"slider\";a:8:{i:854;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:113:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/29-Image-Carousel-Identity-Theft-Slide-11.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:52:\"29 – Image Carousel – Identity Theft – Slide 1\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:52:\"29 – Image Carousel – Identity Theft – Slide 1\";s:7:\"caption\";s:353:\"Whether you’re traveling or running errands, it’s tempting to plug into public Wi-Fi to pass the time or get some work done. While a business might do its best to establish firewalls on its Wi-Fi network, a cybercriminal could tap into the network and access your sensitive files. Here are the top places to practice safety when connecting to Wi-Fi.\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:855;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:113:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/29-Image-Carousel-Identity-Theft-Slide-21.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:52:\"29 – Image Carousel – Identity Theft – Slide 2\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:52:\"29 – Image Carousel – Identity Theft – Slide 2\";s:7:\"caption\";s:282:\"<strong>Hotels:</strong> It’s hard to imagine staying at a hotel without Wi-Fi capabilities. Free Internet has become a norm of a guest experience, but you risk accessing an unsecure network. Make sure to avoid checking sensitive documents and change your passwords regularly. [1]\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:856;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:113:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/29-Image-Carousel-Identity-Theft-Slide-31.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:52:\"29 – Image Carousel – Identity Theft – Slide 3\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:52:\"29 – Image Carousel – Identity Theft – Slide 3\";s:7:\"caption\";s:361:\"<strong>Coffee Shops:</strong> You might think your banking app is for your eyes only, but the reality is that a host of criminals might be reviewing your purchases along with you. Public networks can leave your information exposed to hackers, which allows them to use programs that guess passwords, gain access to information and steal a person\'s identity. [1]\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:857;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:113:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/29-Image-Carousel-Identity-Theft-Slide-41.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:52:\"29 – Image Carousel – Identity Theft – Slide 4\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:52:\"29 – Image Carousel – Identity Theft – Slide 4\";s:7:\"caption\";s:282:\"<strong>Restaurants:</strong> While enjoying a fantastic meal, you might be tempted to buy a few movie tickets for after dinner. However – it’s best not to make any financial transactions or use credit cards on public Wi-Fi because that could leave your information exposed. [2]\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:858;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:113:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/29-Image-Carousel-Identity-Theft-Slide-51.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:52:\"29 – Image Carousel – Identity Theft – Slide 5\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:52:\"29 – Image Carousel – Identity Theft – Slide 5\";s:7:\"caption\";s:301:\"<strong>The Park:</strong> The only thing that beats springtime in the park, is springtime in the park with free Wi-Fi. You probably wouldn’t share your personal files with the stranger sitting next to you on a park bench, so make sure you aren’t doing it involuntarily on an unsecure network. [2]\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:859;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:113:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/29-Image-Carousel-Identity-Theft-Slide-61.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:52:\"29 – Image Carousel – Identity Theft – Slide 6\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:52:\"29 – Image Carousel – Identity Theft – Slide 6\";s:7:\"caption\";s:298:\"<strong>Airports: </strong>During long layovers, we all get the urge to tap into the public Wi-Fi to pass the time, but you should always make sure safety is a priority. Limit the type of business you conduct and adjust the security settings on your device to limit who can access your machine. [3]\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:865;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:113:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/29-Image-Carousel-Identity-Theft-Slide-82.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:52:\"29 – Image Carousel – Identity Theft – Slide 8\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:52:\"29 – Image Carousel – Identity Theft – Slide 8\";s:7:\"caption\";s:248:\"<strong>The Office:</strong> Nowadays, it’s easy to take work away from the desk.  So, before you open that confidential document on your phone, be sure you’re accessing your work’s network by using a secure Virtual Private Network (VPN). [2]\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:1013;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:110:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/MetLife-Defender-Logo-Image-Galleries3.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:39:\"MetLife-Defender-Logo—Image-Galleries\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:39:\"MetLife-Defender-Logo—Image-Galleries\";s:7:\"caption\";s:280:\"Ensure your safety no matter the location: MetLife Defender can help protect you by tracking your data and safeguarding your personal information. \n\n<a href=\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/identity-theft-protection/\">Click here </a>to find out more about identity theft.\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}}s:6:\"config\";a:12:{s:4:\"type\";s:7:\"default\";s:12:\"slider_theme\";s:4:\"base\";s:12:\"slider_width\";i:800;s:13:\"slider_height\";i:450;s:10:\"transition\";s:4:\"fade\";s:8:\"duration\";i:5000;s:5:\"speed\";i:250;s:6:\"gutter\";i:20;s:6:\"slider\";i:0;s:7:\"classes\";a:1:{i:0;s:0:\"\";}s:5:\"title\";s:50:\"The Top 7 Wi-Fi Networks Putting Your Data at Risk\";s:4:\"slug\";s:50:\"the-top-7-wi-fi-networks-putting-