	(443,7,'2014-07-11 18:26:31','2014-07-11 18:26:31','<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-445\" src=\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/42-220991701-3000x2000.jpg\" alt=\"Woman Holding Credit Card\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" /></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><em>Protecting yourself at home and on the run</em></span></p>\r\n<p>We’ve all been using the Web long enough to know the basics of Internet protection—from creating strong passwords to deleting suspicious emails. But often we set those rules aside for the convenience of having the Internet at our fingertips.</p>\r\n<p>Meeting friends at the coffee shop, you may also check email via their unsecured server. Waiting for your daughter at ballet, you might also catch up on banking through their public Wi-Fi. However, unsecured networks are especially tempting to thieves looking for access to your data. So as you walk away with your coffee and balanced checkbook, they can also walk away with your personal information.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Sharing, sharing, everywhere</strong></p>\r\n<p>Your sensitive personal information may be in places you’re unaware of. Whether you visited the doctor with a sick child or your accountant during tax season, your information could be susceptible with these unsuspecting yet trustworthy companies. For example, if the data entry clerk at your doctor’s office is downloading and listening to music while inputting information, the clerk is opening up a P2P network vulnerable to a security breach.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cyber crime is increasing</strong></p>\r\n<p>Perhaps you’ve heard about a friend of a friend who had their data stolen by making a routine purchase at the local grocery store. While you may shrug this off as an unlikely occurrence, it’s actually more common than you think. In fact, 13.1 million consumers suffered identity fraud in 2013.<sup>1</sup> Thieves have developed ways to use software remotely to extract credit and debit card data from inside a store. This means your trip to pick up milk and bread could be a dangerous one.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Protect yourself and your information</strong></p>\r\n<p>In the end, we all love the convenience that our smart devices and the Web offer. However, we need to be smarter than those devices in order to keep our information safe. That’s why MetLife Defender is here. MetLife Defender provides comprehensive protection against the full range of online threats with round-the-clock security to stop these threats before they occur.</p>\r\n<p><strong>If you’d like to have the peace of mind 24/7 security provides, <a href=\"https://www.metlifedefender.com/register/plan/?\">enroll with MetLife Defender</a> today.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">1.Sehgal, Vikram and Jeff Wray. (2013, February 27). <em>Online Retail Forecast, 2012 to 2017</em>. Forrester Research.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">L0614379036[exp0615][All States][DC]</span></p>','A Latte…and a Little Data, To Go','','draft','open','open','','a-latte-and-a-little-data-to-go-2','','','2014-07-25 16:46:31','2014-07-25 16:46:31','',0,'https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/?p=443',0,'post','',0),
