	(986,2,'2014-08-12 19:56:27','2014-08-12 19:56:27','<p><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-839\" src=\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/17-Article-Prescription-Fraud-7-8-14-Image-3000x2151.jpg\" alt=\"17 - Article - Prescription Fraud 7 8 14 Image\" width=\"3000\" height=\"2151\" />Terri arrives at the emergency room after a car accident.  Doctors immediately review her electronic medical records. They note the prescription drugs she’s been taking, and make decisions about her care based on that information. The problem: Terri’s not taking any drugs.</p>\r\n<p>Peter calls his insurance company to inquire about the coverage of his new cholesterol medication. The provider informs Peter that coverage of that medication has been denied because he is currently being prescribed a different brand of cholesterol medicine. But there is a bigger issue for Peter – he’s not taking any cholesterol prescription pills now. </p>\r\n<p>Terri and Peter are victims of prescription and medical fraud, and this type of theft is on the uptick in the United States.  1.84 million people were victims of medical identity fraud in 2013 with the out-of-pocket cost to consumers reaching $12.3 billion.<sup>1  </sup>  </p>\r\n<p>The costs of prescription fraud are personal and financial. Correcting medical records, receiving the wrong treatment, clearing your name, and paying for services you never received are time-consuming, frustrating and often costly experiences.</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"margin:0 139px 20px 20px;\">Here are 5 tips to help protect yourself and your family against prescription identity theft:</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Never buy prescriptions from unauthorized websites.</li>\r\n<li>Carefully review all insurance bills and Explanation of Benefits statements that come in the mail. Immediately report charges for services you have not received.</li>\r\n<li>Keep medical bills and receipts in a secured location, and only for as long as you need them. Shred all medical paperwork before disposing of it.</li>\r\n<li>Report lost or stolen insurance cards.</li>\r\n<li>Take action and let MetLife Defender proactively monitor your medical identification information so it doesn’t fall into the wrong hands and lead to identity theft.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">1. Ponemon Institute. (2014) <em>2013 Survey on Medical Identity Theft</em>. Retrieved from <a href=\"http://medidfraud.org/2013-survey-on-medical-identity-theft/\">http://medidfraud.org/2013-survey-on-medical-identity-theft/</a></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"> </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">L0714384027[exp0715][All States][DC]</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n','Prescription Fraud','','inherit','open','open','','837-revision-v1','','','2014-08-12 19:56:27','2014-08-12 19:56:27','',837,'https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/uncategorized/837-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(987,7,'2014-08-13 14:51:53','2014-08-13 14:51:53','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-485\" src=\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/WhereIsMyData_Infographic_hires_060311.jpg\" alt=\"DM132_D5535_WhereIsMyData_Infographic 2\" width=\"800\" height=\"674\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-style: italic;\">Where did I put my keys? Where on earth did my cellphone go? Did I leave my purse in the car?</p>\r\n<p>You ask yourself these questions every day, but do you ever wonder, <em>“Where is my data?” </em>If not, it’s a question you should start asking! Having this knowledge allows you to keep better track of your personal information.</p>\r\n<p>We can’t help ourselves. It’s become commonplace to depend on apps, websites and a slew of online resources to buy items, review bank account information and send emails every day. Anytime you enter your email address, connect on Facebook, or make an online purchase with your credit card, you are transmitting personally identifiable information that could end up in the wrong hands.</p>\r\n<p>And sometimes, it does.</p>\r\n<p>The vast majority of identity theft incidents—about 85 percent—involve the fraudulent use of accessible account information. An average of 12 million Americans fall victim to identity fraud annually.<sup>1</sup> And in 2013, financial losses totaling $21 billion were attributed to cybercrime.<sup>2</sup></p>\r\n<p>If your data is lost or stolen, the effects can be stressful and devastating. MetLife Defender is a proactive, comprehensive solution that will protect your data and help you avoid these risks.</p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.metlifedefender.com/register/plan/?\">Enroll in MetLife Defender today</a></strong> <strong>so we can monitor your information and keep you safe online. </strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">1. Bureau of Justice Statistics. http://www.bjs.gov/index.cfm?ty=pbdetail&amp;iid=4821. Retrieved February 2014.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">2. Javelin Strategy &amp; Research. <em>2013 Identity Theft Fraud Statistics from Statistic Brain, U.S. Department of Justice</em>, 2013.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"> </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">L0514375772[exp0515][All States][DC]</span></p>','Where is Your Data?','','inherit','open','open','','419-revision-v1','','','2014-08-13 14:51:53','2014-08-13 14:51:53','',419,'https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/uncategorized/419-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(988,7,'2014-08-13 16:09:07','2014-08-13 16:09:07','<p>Your kids use the Internet on a day-to-day basis to stay connected with friends and surf the Web. With the amount of time they spend online, it’s important to know what sites they visit and who they are communicating with. Keep your kids protected by being in-the-know about potential online threats.</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-989\" src=\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/31-Infographic-Cyber-Safety-for-Kids-+-Teens_FINAL-page-001-1088x3000.jpg\" alt=\"31 - Infographic - Cyber Safety for Kids + Teens_FINAL-page-001\" width=\"1088\" height=\"3000\" /></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">L0814386378[exp0815][All States][DC]</span></p>','Cyber Safety for Kids + Teens','','publish','open','open','','cyber-safety-for-kids-teens','','','2014-08-13 16:09:52','2014-08-13 16:09:52','',0,'https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/?p=988',0,'post','',0),
