pan style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">1. Patchin, J. W. &amp; Hinduja, S. (2010). Cyberbullying and self-esteem. Journal of School Health, 80(12), 614-621. Retrieved from: http://www.cyberbullying.us/cyberbullying_and_self_esteem_research_fact_sheet.pdf</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">2. Cyber Bullying: Statistics and Tips. I-SAFE America Survey. Retrieved from: http://www.bullyingstatistics.org/content/bullying-statistics.html</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">3. “Cyberbullying FAQ for Teens.” National Crime Prevention Council. http://www.ncpc.org/topics/cyberbullying/cyberbullying-faq-for-teens</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"> L0614379031[exp0615][All States][DC]</span></p>','Cyberbullying: Just a Buzzword or a Legitimate Problem?','','inherit','open','open','','661-autosave-v1','','','2014-08-15 19:30:06','2014-08-15 19:30:06','',661,'https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/uncategorized/661-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(1015,8,'2014-08-19 17:43:22','2014-08-19 17:43:22','<p><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1016\" src=\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/11-Article-The-Toll-of-Identity-Theft-How-it-Happens-Image-3000x2000.jpg\" alt=\"Man working on computer and holding credit card\" width=\"3000\" height=\"2000\" /></p>\r\n<p>It’s in the news. It’s on your news feed. It may even be in your credit report. We’re talking about identity theft, and every year it affects the lives of millions.[1]</p>\r\n<p>Identity theft occurs when a stranger or family member wrongfully uses your personal information to access your money, fill a prescription in your name, and in the worst cases, assume your full identity to commit crimes. Unfortunately, it becomes more prevalent each year.  It has been reported that one American falls victim to identity theft every three seconds,[2] contributing to a total financial loss of $21 billion,<sup>2</sup> and in 2013, identity theft led the Federal Trade Commission’s list of top consumer complaints.[3]</p>\r\n<p>In today’s digital world, it’s difficult to keep track of where you leave your data - whether you’re online banking through public Wi-Fi, disclosing your personal information over the phone, or checking out at a store you trust without knowing its security has been breached - your information could be at risk.</p>\r\n<p>If your identity is stolen, you may struggle for years trying to recover. The average victim who detects fraud quickly spends about 165 hours repairing the damage done by the creation of new fraudulent accounts, and spends 58 hours repairing the damage done to existing accounts.[4]</p>\r\n<p>That’s why it’s important to safeguard your Social Security Number, bank and credit card numbers, birthday and addresses so that information doesn’t fall into the wrong hands. Take action to protect your data and yourself from identity theft by enrolling in MetLife Defender.</p>\r\n<p>MetLife Defender provides proactive and comprehensive protection for more than 25 different personal data points, and will work to remediate threats, notify the member and include recommended actions if necessary.</p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://metlifedefender.com/register/plan/\">Click here to sign up</a> and learn more about how MetLife Defender helps provide peace of mind.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">[1] Pascual, Alphonse and Sarah Miller. (2014, February<em>). 2014 Identity Fraud Report</em>. Javelin Strategy. Retrieved from https://www.javelinstrategy.com/news/1467/92/A-New-Identity-Fraud-Victim-Every-Two-Seconds-in-2013-According-to-Latest-Javelin-Strategy-Research-Study/d,pressRoomDetail</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">[2] Pascual, Alphonse and Sarah Miller. (2013, February). <em>2013 Identity Fraud Report</em>. Javelin Strategy. Retrieved from https://www.javelinstrategy.com/news/1387/92/1</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">[3] (2014, February 27).<em> FTC Announces Top National Consumer Complaints for 2013</em>. Federal Trade Commission. Retrieved from http://www.ftc.gov/news-events/press-releases/2014/02/ftc-announces-top-national-consumer-complaints-2013</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">[4] Javelin Strategy &amp; Research. <em>2012 Identity Fraud Report: Social Media and Mobile Forming the New Fraud Frontier</em>, 2012.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">L0814387330[exp0815][All States][DC]</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','The Toll of Identity Theft: How it Happens and the Damage it Causes','','publish','open','open','','the-toll-of-identity-theft-how-it-happens-and-the-damage-it-causes-2','','','2014-08-19 17:44:10','2014-08-19 17:44:10','',0,'https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/?p=1015',0,'post','',0),
